25|$|The {{following}} season, McCarthy kept Wolves in the Premier League, {{his first}} success {{at this level}} in three attempts. The club assured safety with two games to spare, eventually finishing 15th, their best league finish since 1979–80, and their first ever survival in the modern Premier League. However, {{in the process of}} keeping the team in the top division, Wolves and McCarthy were fined £25,000 for fielding a weakened team for a fixture at Manchester United and thus breaking the Premier League rule E20. The Premier League also stated that the club had failed to fulfil its obligations to the league and other clubs in the <b>utmost</b> <b>good</b> <b>faith</b> and was therefore in breach of Rule B13.|$|E
