50|$|Despite {{rejecting the}} notion of <b>utmost</b> <b>good</b> <b>faith,</b> the court in M&F v Oudtshoorn did not set out {{the content of the}} {{requirement}} of good faith as it pertains to insurance contracts. Accordingly, past authority which dealt with the content of {{the notion of}} <b>utmost</b> <b>good</b> <b>faith</b> must still be consulted for guidance, while bearing in mind that, in principle, any duty concerned is not a duty of exceptional good faith, but simply one of good faith.|$|E
